$ Excel functions: row and column

`row` and `column` return the row and column number of the current cell or referenced → Microsoft/Office/Excel#excel-cell-address[address].

gh|about-Excel|/functions/row-column.bas||

{ Using address() together with row() and column() to create a reference

 `=→ Microsoft/Office/Excel/functions/address[address](row() + y, column() + x)` is quite usefule to create a *reference* to cell that has a given relative distance from
  the cell that contains the formula.

  See also → Microsoft/Office/Excel/functions/address#xls-func-address-ref-cell[this link].

}

